description:
&lt;p&gt;The Oncology Day case Unit is a developing area, and we see on average 500 patients per month.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate must be able to work in a busy and fast paced environment and co-ordinate the safe transfer of patients to base wards whilst delivering a high standard of care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a management team that is both innovative and proactive in ensuring a high quality care is delivered to our patients. We are keen to encourage developments in line with Trust policy and working in new ways. We recognise responsibility to ensure that staff are developed and stimulated within their environment in order to achieve vision and deliver care that reflects the values and behaviours of the Trust. We offer excellent opportunities for career progression, training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a outpatient administrator to join a diverse and motivated team that is dedicated to the development of specialist clinical skills and the delivery of high quality and safe care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who is well organised with good time management skills, enthusiastic, confident and self-motivated. Good verbal and written communication skills are essential and you must be able to prioritise your own work load. If you enjoy a challenge and like working a part of a team then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
